This paper deals with the analysis and control of power systems, which involves the use of algorithms and computational methods to optimize the performance of the system. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which deals with the modeling, analysis, and control of complex systems. The paper also involves the use of graph theory and network analysis, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a method for improving the robustness of the system, which involves the use of optimization algorithms, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
